generate module¶

This program simply prints the first 100 Prime numbers in a csv file

Extended Description.

This Python file sends 100 to the primemodule and then puts that output into a variable that is then put into a csv file.

generate.main()¶

This drives the program and uses other defined functions in other python files

There are no arguments being sent to this function. it sends and integer and a filename to another function.

Returns:

A csv file that will be in the same file as this python file.

Exceptions:

When anything goes wrong a message will display.
